<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1438" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1438">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">026 China/7–2849: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Macdonald</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                            the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-28T14:00:00+09:00">July 28,
                                1949—2 p. m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received July 28—12:41 p. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>324. Because of past cases where Chinese Government agents have caused
                        “popular” demonstrations against foreigners in official disfavor, request
                        maximum advance notice release date of White Paper. Sent Department,
                        repeated Canton 136.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Macdonald</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>